-- Red Wings Defeat Blackhawks 4-1 to Tie NHL Playoff Series at 1-1
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-05-18T19:47:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-18/red-wings-defeat-blackhawks-4-1-to-tie-nhl-playoff-series-at-1-1.html
The  Detroit Red Wings  beat the
Chicago Blackhawks 4-1 to tie their National Hockey League
second-round playoff series at one game each.  Damien Brunner and Brendan Smith scored in the second
period to give Detroit a 2-1 lead at the United Center in
Chicago. Johan Franzen and Valtteri Filppula then added goals in
the third period.  Patrick Kane  scored in the first period for Chicago, which
won the opening game 4-1 three days.  Game 3 in the best-of-seven Western Conference series will
be played May 20 in Detroit.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  